{{Quote|A technique that makes it possible to detach one's mind from coarse sensations. The secret to overcoming physical pain lies in the nonphysical. A master of this technique can endure any torture and withstand any injury.|Darth Bane, ''Book of Sith''|<ref name="Book of Sith" />}}
'''Crucitorn''' was a [[Force power/Legends|technique]] for enduring physical pain with [[The Force/Legends|the Force]].<ref name="TNEGTC" />

==Description==
Crucitorn was a [[Force power/Legends|technique]] for enduring physical pain or transcending it entirely through [[The Force/Legends|the Force]].<ref name="TNEGTC" /> The [[Sith/Legends|Sith]] classified the technique as part of their [[Mind]] focus or school.<ref name="Book of Sith" />

==Applications==
{{Quote|Ancient Jedi learned that the power of the Force could be used to ease pain, heal wounds, and cure various afflictions, and that these healing arts were effective on ordinary beings as well as Force-users.|Tionne Solusar, ''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force''|<ref name="JvS">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref>}}
By detaching their mind, a [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] or other Force user could endure any manner of wound or withstand even the worst tortures.<ref name="Book of Sith" />

==Users==
{{Quote|Thought this was a Jedi technique! At least that's what Master Koth told me.|Quinlan Vos, ''Book of Sith''|<ref name="Book of Sith" />}}
Crucitorn was used by [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]]<ref name="TNEGTC" /> and [[Sith/Legends|Sith]]. The technique was known by the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]]. Details regarding the technique were mentioned in his [[The Rule of Two|essay]], which, many [[Standard year/Legends|years]] later, was added to the ''[[Book of Sith]]'', a compilation of historical writings collected in one volume by [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]].<ref name="Book of Sith" /> During the [[Mandalorian Wars]], some of the [[Revanchist]]s practiced Crucitorn.<ref name="Fringe">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/FringeStatPack|text=Fringe Stat Pack}}</ref> During the [[Great Peace of the Republic]], Crucitorn was practiced by [[Eeth Koth/Legends|Eeth Koth]], a [[Zabrak/Legends|Zabrak]] [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]].<ref name="TNEGTC" /> Upon reading about the technique in the ''Book of Sith'', [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Quinlan Vos/Legends|Quinlan Vos]] was surprised to learn the technique was used by the Sith.<ref name="Book of Sith" />

